reviews.review: This movie hit me hard with so many feelings and closed so many gaps that earlier on made me upset about being missing. The first of this trilogy was very promising in what was to come and the second, well, it wasn't that great. A ton of nonsensical situations that never got closure. This movie closed the trilogy with the ending we all needed after what came from the other two and more!
Huge letdown. Too big. They let the series get too sloppy.

It was great! It has everything to make fans happy! If you don't like it, you are not a Star Wars fan. A movie with a heartbreaking ending, but a perfect one.
I laughed, I had fear, I cried, I had to say goodbye to my faborite character. But I'm so happy I have no words to describe this perfect film.
You cannot prepare for this. It’s incredible.

Disconnected and scattered, people pleasing mush. This sold out franchise wanders through a beautiful computerised landscape with beige and unbeguiled comrades, borrowing impactful moments from more deserving films.
This movie was a perfect closure to the Skywalker Saga, it tied up a lot with the previous films. I was on the edge of my seat with tears of joy. This movie really hit the heart for Star War fans

Une honte absolue ! Disney, Kathleen Kennedy, JJ Abrams et Johnson : DEHORS !
Vous avez tué Star Wars, ne comptez pas sur moi pour Disney+ ou tout autre SW sous votre franchise.

It was fan service yes, but a more enjoyable movie experience than TLJ. People are complaining about macguffins and poor story but I don't believe Star wars have ever being the most amazing stories in cinema. I enjoyed it, I'll happily watch and enjoy it again too.

In a classic sense of movie critics being completely out of touch with what makes a movie "good", it seems like the bar for this movie has been made to be considerably h higher than it was for any of the other Star Wars movies that preceded it.  

It's a shame, too - this is a fun ride, and a worthy entry into the saga.  It's easily the best of the new trilogy, certainly better than any of the prequels, and potentially even better than Return of the Jedi.
Much better then the last one.
